-- Balfour, Enel, Ferrovial, Prysmian, Tamburi, Weir: European Equity Preview
-- B y   T a r a   L a c h a p e l l e
-- 2010-11-18T21:54:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/balfour-enel-ferrovial-tamburi-weir-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are from the previous close.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  advanced 1.4 percent to 271.15.
The  Stoxx 50 Index  rose 1.4 percent to 2,587.93. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, gained 1.9
percent to 2,855.23.  Balfour Beatty Plc  (BBY LN): Britain’s biggest builder said
it reached an agreement to acquire some of Rok Plc’s affordable
housing and general construction unit. The shares advanced 0.4
percent to 279.3 pence.  Enel SpA  (ENEL IM): The European Union’s effort to restrict
imported carbon credits is dragging on because of “relentless”
lobbying by companies including Enel SpA, RWE AG and E.ON AG,
the climate group CDM Watch said. Enel gained 0.6 percent to
4.06 euros.  Ferrovial SA  (FER SM): The U.K. competition regulator said
it may reconsider its ruling that Ferrovial’s BAA Ltd. unit must
sell three airports after the U.K. government cancel plans to
build a third runway at Heathrow. The stock rose 0.6 percent to
7.77 euros.  Prysmian SpA  (PRY IM): Clubtre Srl, owned by  Tamburi
Investment Partners  SpA (TIP IM), Angelini Partecipazioni
Finanziarie SpA and d’Amico Societa’ di Navigazione SpA, raised
its stake in the Italian cable maker to 5 percent. Prysmian rose
1 percent to 12.99 euros. Tamburi was unchanged at 1.38 euros.  Weir Group Plc  (WEIR LN): The Glasgow-based engineering
company bought American Hydro Corporation, a U.S. manufacturer
of components for turbines that convert water power into
electricity. Terms of the sale weren’t disclosed. The shares
rose 2.1 percent to 1,725 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Tara Lachapelle  in New York at 
